    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How long does it take for iron gummies to work?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Most people begin to notice improvements in energy levels within 2 to 4 weeks of consistent iron supplementation. However, it takes approximately 2 to 3 months to fully replenish depleted iron stores (ferritin). Your healthcare provider should recheck your iron levels and ferritin after 3 months of supplementation to assess progress. Do not stop taking iron supplements simply because you feel better — continue until your provider confirms that your stores are adequately replenished.' },
    },
