      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Can you take too much iron?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Yes. The Tolerable Upper Intake Level (UL) for iron is 45 mg per day for adults. Excessive iron intake can cause nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, and in severe cases, organ damage. Iron is one of the few minerals the body cannot efficiently excrete, which makes chronic over-supplementation particularly dangerous. Never exceed the recommended dose on the product label, and always have your iron levels tested before starting supplementation. People with hemochromatosis (iron overload disorder) should not take iron supplements.' },
    },
