        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-card-ico">&#x1F33F;</div>
          <h3>Vegans & Vegetarians</h3>
          <p>Plant-based iron (non-heme) is 2 to 3 times less bioavailable than animal-based iron (heme). The NIH recommends that vegetarians consume 1.8x the standard RDA — roughly 32 mg/day for premenopausal women on plant-based diets.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-card-ico">&#x1F3C3;</div>
          <h3>Endurance Athletes</h3>
          <p>Runners and endurance athletes lose iron through foot-strike hemolysis, sweat, and GI microbleeding. Studies show that up to 56% of female distance runners have depleted iron stores, even without overt anemia.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

