      <p>In our 4-week testing panel, BeLive produced the most consistent results across all evaluation criteria. Testers reported noticeable improvements in energy levels by week 2, with none of the severe constipation or nausea commonly associated with ferrous sulfate tablets. The grape flavor received high marks — it effectively masks the metallic taste that plagues many iron supplements. At $0.25 per serving with 18 mg of iron plus vitamin C, BeLive offers the best value-to-effectiveness ratio of any iron gummy we tested.</p>

